author: Caloy Lozada
title: DA Western Visayas launches mobile veterinary lab to boost animal healthcare
text:
To ensure that government services reach rural farmers, the Department of Agriculture (DA) Western Visayas has introduced a mobile veterinary and molecular laboratory.
This initiative aims to bolster animal healthcare by bringing medical and diagnostic services closer to livestock and poultry farmers across the region.
The newly acquired mobile lab will be operated by the Regional Animal Diagnostic and Disease Laboratory team, enhancing the region’s capacity for animal health monitoring and disease control.
This mobile unit will also facilitate the accurate collection and handling of specimens, working in collaboration with various local government units (LGUs).
DA-Western Visayas hails the new mobile lab as a game changer, particularly for farmers in Geographically Isolated and Disadvantaged Areas (GIDA), making essential healthcare services more accessible.
The mobile lab will diagnose a range of animal infections, including Nipah Virus, Japanese Encephalitis, Tuberculosis, Swine Flu, and Monkeypox.
According to Zarlina Cuello, Regional Technical Director for Research and Regulations, this new asset will significantly contribute to safeguarding animal health, mitigating infectious diseases, and promoting sustainable practices among stakeholders in Western Visayas.
The agency is also considering expanding the mobile lab’s services to include Real-Time Polymerase Chain Reaction (RT-PCR) tests, further enhancing its diagnostic capabilities.

title: Imágenes impactantes: así quedó el túnel de la vía al Llano tras explosión de tractomula
text:
Luego de que fuera controlada la emergencia, solo hasta el miércoles 27 de diciembre las autoridades lograron entrar al túnel para verificar su estado y hacer un balance de los daños.
Imágenes impactantes: así quedó el túnel de la vía al Llano tras explosión de tractomula December 28th, 8:28amDecember 28th, 8:28amdrodriguezb
El pasado martes 26 de diciembre, un grave accidente se registró a la altura del túnel de Quebrada Blanca, en la vía que conecta a Bogotá con Villavicencio, siniestro que provocó el cierre total de este corredor vial.
Según se conoció, un vehículo de carga se habría quedado sin frenos, lo que hizo que el conductor perdiera el control del vehículo y terminara volcándose y posteriormente explotando, provocando un voraz incendio en el interior de túnel.
Te puede interesar: Video: así fue el trágico accidente de tractomula en túnel de la vía al llano
El camión pertenece a la empresa CTC Cootranscopetrol y transportaba en su interior un material inflamable conocido como nafta, lo que provocó la fuerte explosión, según informaron las autoridades.
Bomberos de Villavicencio, Cáqueza y Guayabetal llegaron a la zona a atender la emergencia, sin embargo, al tratarse de un líquido inflamable, también se requirió de un equipo especializado en sustancias peligrosas.
Sobre el conductor del vehículo accidentado, este fue rescatado con quemaduras del 84 % de su cuerpo y fue trasladado a un centro médico en Villavicencio. No obstante, debido a la gravedad de sus heridas será remitido a Bogotá para recibir atención especializada.
Revelan imágenes del túnel tras fuerte explosión Luego de que fuera controlada la emergencia, que se registró sobre las 2:40 de la tarde, solo hasta el miércoles 27 de diciembre las autoridades lograron entrar al túnel para verificar su estado y hacer un balance de los daños.
En redes sociales se conocieron imágenes que dejaron sorprendidos a los usuarios, no solo del momento exacto del accidente, sino también del estado en el que quedó el túnel.
En las imágenes se ve que la fuerte explosión e incendio terminó incinerando todo el corredor vial, pues en su interior este se ve completamente quemado, dejando en evidencia lo grave que fue el siniestro.
El ingeniero Fernando Castillo, director de operación de Coviandina, explicó que aún no es claro el tiempo que estará cerrado el túnel Quebrada Blanca de la vía al Llano.
Asimismo, señaló que tras el accidente se están tomando medidas debido al exceso de velocidad que se registra con gran frecuencia en esta zona.

author: Guy Hirst
title: Nearly 1000 'illegal school' inspections in a decade - but just 7 prosecutions
text:
A new Ofsted report into inspections of suspected unregistered schools has revealed an escalation in England’s illegal school scandal. Since 2022 Ofsted has logged 200 referrals of suspected unregistered schools per year, compared with an annual average of fewer than 150 before then. Since it set up a specialist enforcement team in 2016, it has opened 1,574 investigations, carried out 945 inspections and issued 212 warning notices, yet secured only seven prosecutions of seven settings – resulting in 21 convictions.
The large drop from the number of inspections to the number of prosecutions is because Ofsted doesn’t have sufficient powers to prosecute in most cases – allowing proprietors of illegal schools to continue operating with impunity. The Children’s Wellbeing and Schools Bill will solve this problem. Humanists UK is supporting these areas of the Bill and has said the latest review shows why it is essential.
Illegal religious schools – a form of child abuse
Humanists UK has campaigned on this issue for more than a decade, supporting whistleblowers, collating testimony from former pupils and providing evidence that prompted Ofsted to create the unregistered schools unit. At least 6,000 children are in illegal religious schools in England. Many of these establishments masquerade as centres for ‘part-time tuition’, thereby exploiting loopholes in the law. In reality they operate full-time, and put children at risk with no regard for proper health, safety, or safeguarding.
Many operate from cramped industrial units or private homes and, according to Ofsted, health and safety and safeguarding problems are often found including blocked fire exits, unsafe wiring, unsanitary facilities and adults who have never undergone safeguarding checks. Sometimes the pupils trapped in them do nothing all day bar learn religious texts. Many leave school unprepared for life in modern Britain – perhaps not speaking English, despite having grown up here. Child sexual abuse is well documented.
Of the 669 settings inspected since 2016, 18% were confirmed to definitely be faith-based. For many of the others it is impossible to know.
Children’s Wellbeing and Schools Bill will increase Ofsted’s powers
The Children’s Wellbeing and Schools Bill, now before the House of Lords, would define such settings as independent educational institutions – a class of institution that can then be regulated out of existence through Ofsted powers to inspect.
It will also introduce a national register for home-schooled children, making it harder for illegal providers to operate.
Humanists UK’s Education Campaigns Manager Kieran Aldred said:
‘Ofsted’s findings reveal the hundreds of illegal schools operating across England, with risks to the safety of children who attend them. But the handful of prosecutions indicates limitations of Ofsted’s ability to take action against these settings, many of which are dogmatic faith-based institutions. We welcome the provisions in the Children’s Wellbeing and School Bill to address these problems.’

title: Anuncian Retiro de Perrito Corredor "El Chicles" Tras Sufrir Fractura en Tijuana | N+
text: "El Chicles", Famoso Perro Corredor, Se Retira Tras Sufrir Fractura La noticia, fue dada a conocer a través de redes sociales, donde se informó que sufrió una fractura de fémur en la pierna derecha y cadera | N+ - COMPARTE: La noticia, fue dada a conocer a través de redes sociales, donde se informó que sufrió una fractura de fémur en la pierna derecha y cadera N+ COMPARTE: El famoso perro corredor de Tijuana “El Chicles”, que ganó fama nacional al ser el primer perro en registrar un tiempo de 13:38 en una carrera de 5 kilómetros, se retirará de las competencias. La noticia fue dada a conocer a través de redes sociales, donde se informó que sufrió una fractura de fémur en la pierna derecha y cadera. Esta situación ha dejado al perrito con dificultades para poder levantarse y caminar, ya que según informaron, solo puede apoyarse en tres patas. Su dueño compartió que los costos para realizar la cirugía son muy elevados, por lo que solicitó el apoyo de la comunidad tijuanense para poder cubrir los gastos, por lo que pueden comunicarse a través de sus redes. Este perrito no solo es un corredor de renombre, sino también una figura querida en la ciudad fronteriza, donde incluso tiene un mural gracias a su desempeño en las calles de Tijuana. Además de su récord mundial en los 5 kilómetros, ha ganado múltiples competencias de 5 y 10 kilómetros, convirtiéndose en un gran ejemplo de perseverancia. Te recomendamos: DEPB

title: Staying dry and beautiful in the Midlands this weekend
text: COLUMBIA, S.C. (WIS) - With winds flipping back out of the southwest our temperatures will be on the rise the next couple days with highs in the 80s Sunday and Monday. First Alert Weather Headlines: - Another cool night with lows in the 40s. - Highs for Sunday and Monday rebound to the 80s. - Temps tumble back down Tuesday with highs near 70 degrees. First Alert Weather Summary It was a gorgeous start to the weekend with bright sunny skies warming highs into the upper 70s. Once the sun goes down our temperatures will cool off quickly again as lows will drop into the mid to upper 40s for the Midlands. Sunday will continue the warming trend for the Carolinas as high pressure slides off to the east, out into the Atlantic, causing our winds to now come out of the southwest pumping in warming air to the region as highs will climb to the low to mid 80s. But it will be another great day to head out to the South Carolina State Fair as we will have sunny skies and low humidity levels. Monday will be another warm day with highs in the 80s under mostly sunny skies. Late Monday into Tuesday a strong cold front sweeps through the Carolinas ushering in a blast of cool, Canadian air. Highs Tuesday through Friday will be below average in the 60s to lower 70s. It will also get quite cold first thing in the mornings with lows dipping down into the lower 40s with some rural locations maybe falling into the upper 30s. Also the dry conditions look to continue for the Midlands as it has now been 15 days since our last day with rain and looking ahead we are not tracking any rain chances over the next 10 days so we could be looking at a completely dry October. First Alert Weather Forecast Tonight: Clear and cool with lows in the mid to upper 40s. Sunday: Sunshine continues and warmer. Highs in the mid-80s. Monday: Mostly sunny skies. Warm, with highs in the low to mid-80s. Tuesday: A few passing clouds. Cooler, with highs nearing 70 degrees. Wednesday: More sunshine but cool with highs in the mid-60s. Morning lows in the lower 40s. Thursday: Another sunny but cool day with highs in the 60s after starting out in the lower 40s. Feel more informed, prepared, and connected with WIS. title: Servette 2-1 Chelsea: Post-Match Chelsea Player Ratings
text:
Chelsea did not have as comfortable a night as they would have imagined going into the match, as they lost the Conference League Play-off second leg 2-1 to Servette.
Despite the late scare, the Blues still progress into the Conference League
Similar to the first leg, it was a
Christopher Nkunku penalty which opened the scoring on the night to make it 3-0 on aggregate.
Although it looked as if the tie would be over after that goal,
Servette did brilliantly to come back into the tie scoring a goal in each half to put pressure on the West Londoners late on.
Here is how each player performed:
Filip Jorgensen - 6
The Danish goalkeeper did not have as good a performance as he did in the first leg.
Although he made a couple of decent saves, he was poor on Servette's second goal of the match.
Axel Disasi - 5
Disasi was caught out of position for the first goal.
The French defender also did not look composed on the ball many times throughout the match.
Tosin Adarabioyo - 6
Adarabioyo was solid for large portions of the game and he does look composed playing out from the back.
However, he should have definitely done better for Servette's second.
Benoit Badiashile - 5
Very poor for the first goal as it looked as if he had switched off for a split second.
The Frenchman also does not fill you with confidence when he is on the ball.
Renato Veiga - 6
The Portuguese summer signing had a solid enough performance.
Although he was not perfect, you can tell that there is definitely a player in there and perhaps this was good business from Chelsea.
Enzo Fernandez - 6
He was controlling the match at times with his passing, but the final ball was lacking.
The Argentine does not offer enough defensively though, as many times he was ran past too easily.
Kiernan Dewsbury-Hall - 5
The midfielder picked up some good positions at times but he lost the ball too often.
The former
Leicester City man's final ball also was not there.
https://www.vavel.com/en/football/2024/08/01/chelsea-fc/1190781-enzo-maresca-very-happy-after-improved-chelsea-performance-in-atlanta.html - 7
As he did in the first leg, Nkunku scored the penalty for the Blues.
The Frenchman also looked like a creative threat throughout the match, and was unlucky to not get another goal or assist.
Noni Madueke - 6
Madueke looked dangerous at times cutting in on the right.
However, the final product was not there as it was against
Wolves on the weekend.
Mykhailo Mudryk - 6
It was a performance that we are used to seeing from the Ukrainian, bright moments and electric pace but no end product.
He did win the penalty for his side and did look better overall than he did in the first leg.
Marc Guiu - 5
The young Spanish striker pressed well as he did in the first leg.
However, other than that he struggled to lead the line and did not have the best of matches.
-
Substitutes
Tyrique George - 7
The young winger grew into the game the longer he was on the pitch.
A creative threat, it looks as if Cobham has another gem on their hands.
Moises Caicedo - 6
Caicedo came on for Enzo and added a bit more durability than his Argentinian counterpart would have done.
It was not a performance to write home about, but he was alright.
Nicolas Jackson - 7
The Senegalese forward came on and definitely was a threat.
He put the ball in the back of the net, but it was ruled out for offside.
Jackson will be leaving this match wondering how he did not get a goal or an assist.
Cole Palmer - 7
Similar to Jackson, the Englishman will be wondering how he did not leave this game with a goal.
Palmer hit the woodwork and also linked well with his teammates in a creative showing off the bench.
